## Quickstart

```bash
cp .env.example .env   # fill in your secrets
{{- if .HasAddon.compose }}
docker compose -f deploy/docker-compose.yml up -d
{{- end }}
make wire              # generate wire_gen.go
make run               # boots the server on the port set in pkg/config/config.yaml
curl http://localhost:8080/healthz
```

## Layout

- `cmd/server` — HTTP entry point
- `cmd/cli` — CLI entry (Cobra root only; add subcommands as you need them)
{{- if .HasPattern.worker }}
- `cmd/worker` — event-driven worker entry point
{{- end }}
- `internal/server/{controller,service,repository,infrastructure,middleware,handler,dto,model,entity}` — server-side code
- `pkg/config` — Viper-backed typed config
- `pkg/database/<db>` — connection stubs (one per selected DB)
{{- if .HasPattern.worker }}
- `pkg/queue` — producer/consumer interfaces
{{- end }}
- `errors/` — `AppError` catalog with stable numeric codes
- `log/` — zap logger with `trace_id`-aware context helpers
- `mock/`, `migration/`, `schema/` — empty starter folders

## Conventions

- File names are `snake_case`.
- Controller structs end with `Controller`; service interfaces with `Service`; repository interfaces with `Repo`.
- Time fields end with `At`, `Time`, or `Duration`.
- DTOs live only in `internal/server/dto/` and never cross into the service layer.
- Secrets always live in `.env`; `pkg/config/config.yaml` is for non-secret structural defaults only.
